5 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Gaming impact study. (1) The department of justice, gambling control
6 division, in conjunction with the gaming advisory council, shall conduct a study of the gaming industry in
7 Montana.
8 (2) The study must utilize a range of data from different sources, including video gambling machine
9 manufacturers, owners, route operators, casino owners, and applicable trend data from Montana and other
10 states.
11 (3) Upon completion of the study, the department shall publish a report that is accessible to the
12 public. The report must include:
13 (a) a comprehensive assessment of the data as it relates to bet limits, payout limits, bonus games,
14 game structure, and other ancillary issues that are deemed relevant;
15 (b) specific information about the methods used for collecting or acquiring data used in the report;
16 and
17 (c) the identification of specific issues for consideration by the legislature and department
18 concerning gaming.
19 (4) The study and report must be completed by December 1, 2026.
